Description . All colonies are digitiform, slightly laterally flattened, tapering toward the rounded apical end and have a short, polyp-free base (
Fig. 15 A,B,C
). They are between 10–53 mm tall, 4–18 mm in diameter at the apex and 4–25 mm in diameter across the holdfast. The polyps are dimorphic, and arranged uniformly over the surface of the colonies. In all colonies the autozooid polyps are completely retracted and surrounded by minute pores representing the siphonozooids.
